                            <h2 class="block-title"><span>District Announcements</span></h2>
<section class="html-wrapper"><div class="html-wrapper-inner" cms-block-content-root>
        <p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"><strong>McCullough Drive-Thru Food Collection</strong><br>McCullough Elementary Staff wants to celebrate and thank our students and their families by supporting the Penn-Trafford Community.  A Drive-Thru food collection will take place on Saturday, May 2, 2020, from 11 am to 1 pm outside at McCullough Elementary.  All food collected will help families in the Penn-Trafford community. </span><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Anyone from the community wanting to give is encouraged to drive through and donate non-perishable food items. McCullough Elementary students and families are invited to drive through and see the McCullough Elementary Staff along the donation path around the school. </span><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> Whether you are donating or not, we would love to see your smiling faces!   </span><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">At the end of the path, those donating will be directed to a Social Distancing Drop Off Station.  At that Station, only one person can exit the car to drop off the donation.  The person donating must wear a mask when getting out of the car.   </span><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Join us and enjoy the drive around the school seeing some familiar faces and making a difference! </span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; text-align: center; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-style: italic; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">A special thank you to the Penn Township Police and </span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; text-align: center; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-style: italic; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">the Claridge Volunteer Fire Department for their ongoing community support. </span></p>
<p class="tinymce-block"><strong>Commencement Date Postponed</strong><br>Commencement was originally scheduled for May 21st is now <em>tentatively</em> rescheduled for Friday, June 26, 2020 at 6:30 pm.</p>
<p class="tinymce-block"><strong>High School Prom</strong><br>Scheduled for May 1 has now been cancelled.  The prom will be replaced with a <strong>Senior Farewell Dinner Dance</strong> at Antonelli's Event Center in Irwin on June 19.  The event, only for seniors, will include dinner and dance, Top 20 and Scholarship Recognition, a senior slideshow and other activities.  Students can wear their prom attire or wear semi-casual attire.  A tentative back up date is July 23.</p>
<p class="tinymce-block"><strong>Footloose High School Musical</strong><br>A possible performance will be announced once social distancing restrictions are lifted.</p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Information for Parents</span></strong></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">If you need Internet resources, Comcast is currently providing services for free for 60 days. Please see the following link for information: </span><a href="https://www.internetessentials.com/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration-line: none;" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.internetessentials.com/&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1584809933945000&amp;usg=AFQjCNErs2ik0TvtCX0kRqe8EcJT4XiP8Q" rel="noopener"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; text-decoration-line: underline; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">https://www.<wbr></wbr>internetessentials.com/</span></a><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> </span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"> </p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">The <em><strong>School Lunch Grab and Go program</strong></em> will continue on Mondays and Wednesdays from 11-1 at the high school. Please remember to just pull up in the front of the school by the nurse’s office entrance, and the meals will be brought to your car. </span><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Trafford Middle will also have the School Lunch Grab and Go program on Mondays and Wednesdays from 11-1. Pick up is at the cafeteria door lower level. <span style="color: #222222;"><span style="font-family: cambria;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">On Monday – meals will be provided for Monday &amp; Tuesday. On Wednesday – meals will be provided for Wednesday, Thursday &amp; Friday. If additional food assistance is needed, please contact our Backpacks-to-Go Program coordinators at 724-744-0302.</span></span></span></span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"> </p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">These are resources that you can use from the state to stay safe and healthy during this time: </span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin: 0pt 30pt 8pt;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">For more information, please refer to the CDC website (</span><a href="https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus" target="_blank" style="text-decoration-line: none;" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1584809933945000&amp;usg=AFQjCNFV4g-h5rbTsZXee5HcAjx2ab3t3Q" rel="noopener"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; text-decoration-line: underline; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">https://www.cdc.gov/<wbr></wbr>coronavirus</span></a><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">) and PA Department of Health (</span><a href="https://www.health.pa.gov/topics/disease/Pages/Coronavirus.aspx" target="_blank" style="text-decoration-line: none;" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.health.pa.gov/topics/disease/Pages/Coronavirus.aspx&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1584809933945000&amp;usg=AFQjCNHrPjQPSerYZ9LzA7A5-JFQG2U9FA" rel="noopener"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; text-decoration-line: underline; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">https://www.health.pa.gov/<wbr></wbr>topics/disease/Pages/<wbr></wbr>Coronavirus.aspx</span></a></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="color: #888888;"> </span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"><span style="font-size: 16px; color: rgba(0,0,0,0.870588); font-family: georgia,serif; background-color: #fafafa;"><em><strong><span style="color: #ff0000;">Please note:</span></strong></em> <em>Per the guidelines for social distancing and the safety and well being of our students, staff and community all Facilities within the Penn-Trafford School District are closed until further notice. This includes Warrior Stadium, Warrior Center, HS Fitness Center, and all district fields/gymnasiums/weight rooms/tennis courts. Thank you for your cooperation as we work through this together.</em> </span></span></p>
